# Help Text
help:
  step1: "Step 1:"
  step1_desc: "Click on the customer tag you want to analyze. For example, you can click on Purchase Amount."
  step2: "Step 2:"
  step2_desc: "Click on your analysis tool. For example, you can click Execute Customer Clustering."
  step3: "Step 3:"
  step3_desc: "Click on view options. For example, you can click Statistical Charts."
  repeat_steps: "Repeat the above steps. For example, if you want to view customer recency, you can repeat the above steps to view analysis results and AI marketing recommendations."

  overview: |
    Customer DNA Analysis is the most comprehensive customer analysis module, providing:
    - 7-dimensional customer DNA metrics
    - Intelligent clustering and segment naming
    - 11 RFM segment profiles
    - AI-driven insights and recommendations

  dna_metrics: |
    7 DNA Dimensions Explanation:

    1. M (Monetary) - Total spending amount, reflects customer value
    2. R (Recency) - Days since last purchase, reflects activity level
    3. F (Frequency) - Number of purchases, reflects loyalty
    4. IPT (Inter-Purchase Time) - Average purchase interval, reflects purchase cycle
    5. CAI (Customer Activity Index) - Comprehensive activity metric
    6. PCV (Past Customer Value) - Historical total value
    7. CRI (Customer Richness Index) - Purchase stability score

  clustering: |
    Intelligent Clustering:
    - Use K-means or hierarchical clustering
    - Automatically find optimal cluster number
    - AI smart segment naming
    - Generate segment feature profiles

    Clustering helps:
    - Identify similar customer groups
    - Develop differentiated strategies
    - Precision marketing deployment
    - Optimize resource allocation

  rfm_segments: |
    11 RFM Segments:

    High-Value Segments:
    1. Champions: Best customers
    2. Loyal Customers: Stable high-value
    3. Can't Lose Them: High-value but churn risk

    Growth Potential Segments:
    4. Potential Loyalists: Can be cultivated
    5. Promising: High order value
    6. Recent Customers: New customers

    Needs Attention Segments:
    7. Need Attention: Cooling down
    8. About to Sleep: Declining activity
    9. At Risk: High churn risk

    Low-Value Segments:
    10. Hibernating: Long-term no interaction
    11. Lost: Already churned

  ai_analysis: |
    AI-Enhanced Analysis:
    Leverage GPT-4 to provide intelligent insights:
    - Metric Description: Interpret business significance of metrics
    - Distribution Insight: Discover distribution characteristics and anomalies
    - Segment Profiling: Generate detailed segment descriptions
    - Marketing Recommendations: Provide precision marketing strategies
    - Churn Prediction: Predict churn and provide recovery recommendations
    - Cross-sell: Discover sales opportunities

  best_practices: |
    Analysis Recommendations:
    1. First review each metric distribution to understand overall customer status
    2. Execute intelligent clustering to identify different segments
    3. Analyze RFM segments to understand customer lifecycle stage
    4. Use AI insights for deep analysis and recommendations
    5. Develop differentiated strategies for different segments
    6. Regularly track segment changes and adjust strategies

# Hints
hints:
  metric_selection: "Click on customer tags to view visualization charts for each tag"
  clustering: "Intelligent clustering automatically finds similar customer groups. Recommend using AI naming feature to generate meaningful names based on group characteristics."
